@endpoint GET /{resourceUri}/providers/Microsoft.ResourceHealth/childAvailabilityStatuses
@desc Lists the historical availability statuses for a single child resource. Use the nextLink property in the response to get the next page of availability status
@required {resourceUri: any # The fully qualified ID of the resource, including the resource name and resource type. Currently the API only support one nesting level resource types : /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/{resource-provider-name}/{parentResourceType}/{parentResourceName}/{resourceType}/{resourceName}}
